  "prompt": "Should i be concerned about pericoronal flap?",
  "response": "A pericoronal flap (or pericoronitis) can be a concern and may require attention. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Symptoms to watch for:\n- Swelling around wisdom tooth\n- Pain or discomfort\n- Difficulty opening mouth\n- Bad breath\n- Fever\n- Swollen lymph nodes\n\n2. Potential risks:\n- Infection spreading\n- Abscess formation\n- Damage to adjacent teeth\n- Severe pain and inflammation\n\n3. When to see a dentist:\n- Persistent symptoms\n- Difficulty eating or drinking\n- Significant pain\n- Signs of infection\n- Fever over 101\u00b0F\n\n4. Treatment options:\n- Antibiotics\n- Cleaning and irrigation\n- Pain management\n- Partial or full wisdom tooth removal\n\n5. Prevention:\n- Good oral hygiene\n- Regular dental check-ups\n- Proper cleaning around wisdom teeth\n\n6. Serious complications:\n- Rare but potential spread of infection\n- Potential jaw bone involvement\n\nRecommendation: Consult a dentist for professional evaluation and personalized advice about your specific situation.",
